<div class="comment-text">
<p>It should also be possible to pass custom values for the TinyMCE init options to the_editor. There are a number of filters you can use too, which you may be able to work with to give different values in different situations (by looking at what is there already). That <em>should</em> give you the flexibility to deal with each differently</p>
</div><!-- .comment-text -->
