<li id="comment-3484" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1 reader has-avatar">
<img alt='Kathy' src='http://2.gravatar.com/avatar/e59280745b3f6f86a4cc6fad485647e9?s=80&#038;r=r' srcset='http://2.gravatar.com/avatar/e59280745b3f6f86a4cc6fad485647e9?s=160&amp;r=r 2x' class='avatar avatar-80 photo' height='80' width='80' /><div class="comment-meta comment-meta-data"><span class="comment-author vcard"><cite class="fn">Kathy</cite></span><!-- .comment-author .vcard --> <span class="published"><abbr class="comment-date" title="Wednesday, August 25th, 2010, 7:28 pm">August 25, 2010</abbr> at <abbr class="comment-time" title="Wednesday, August 25th, 2010, 7:28 pm">7:28 pm</abbr></span> | <a class="permalink" href="http://www.farinspace.com/multiple-wordpress-wysiwyg-visual-editors/#comment-3484" title="Permalink to comment 3484">Permalink</a>  </div>
<div class="comment-text">
<p>i did figure out the answer to my question from above.  in case anybody else would like to use jquery to hide the WP post box based on template&#8230; i added this to the document.ready function:</p>
<pre>
ID,'_wp_page_template',TRUE);
if ('template-home.php' == $template_file ) {
echo "$('#postdivrich').hide();";
} ?&gt;
</pre>
</div><!-- .comment-text -->
