<li id="comment-4241" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1 reader has-avatar">
<img alt='Joh' src='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/a64ef0a8b5361fd7c4abce81011f2f6b?s=80&#038;r=r' srcset='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/a64ef0a8b5361fd7c4abce81011f2f6b?s=160&amp;r=r 2x' class='avatar avatar-80 photo' height='80' width='80' /><div class="comment-meta comment-meta-data"><span class="comment-author vcard"><cite class="fn">Joh</cite></span><!-- .comment-author .vcard --> <span class="published"><abbr class="comment-date" title="Wednesday, September 22nd, 2010, 2:47 pm">September 22, 2010</abbr> at <abbr class="comment-time" title="Wednesday, September 22nd, 2010, 2:47 pm">2:47 pm</abbr></span> | <a class="permalink" href="http://www.farinspace.com/multiple-wordpress-wysiwyg-visual-editors/#comment-4241" title="Permalink to comment 4241">Permalink</a>  </div>
<div class="comment-text">
<p>Got it working!</p>
<p>I added the following before the script and that solved the javascript error.</p>
<pre lang="php">
add_action('admin_init', 'editor_admin_init');
add_action('admin_head', 'editor_admin_head');
function editor_admin_init() {
wp_enqueue_script('word-count');
wp_enqueue_script('post');
wp_enqueue_script('editor');
}
function editor_admin_head() {
wp_tiny_mce();
}
</pre>
<p>The code in this tutorial saved me hours and hours of work, thanks a lot!!</p>
</div><!-- .comment-text -->
</li><!-- .comment -->
