<li id="comment-14643" class="comment even thread-even depth-1 reader has-avatar">
<img alt='kathy' src='http://2.gravatar.com/avatar/e59280745b3f6f86a4cc6fad485647e9?s=80&#038;r=r' srcset='http://2.gravatar.com/avatar/e59280745b3f6f86a4cc6fad485647e9?s=160&amp;r=r 2x' class='avatar avatar-80 photo' height='80' width='80' /><div class="comment-meta comment-meta-data"><span class="comment-author vcard"><cite class="fn">kathy</cite></span><!-- .comment-author .vcard --> <span class="published"><abbr class="comment-date" title="Wednesday, May 4th, 2011, 11:07 am">May 4, 2011</abbr> at <abbr class="comment-time" title="Wednesday, May 4th, 2011, 11:07 am">11:07 am</abbr></span> | <a class="permalink" href="http://www.farinspace.com/multiple-wordpress-wysiwyg-visual-editors/#comment-14643" title="Permalink to comment 14643">Permalink</a>  </div>
<div class="comment-text">
<p>@aaron et al..  the tinyMCE.execInstanceCommand wasn&#8217;t getting the right ID, so it was always defaulting to the final box.  i fixed this by getting the ID of the following texarea (assuming you use Aaron&#8217;s markup).  i used a new variable name b/c i don&#8217;t understand scope and didn&#8217;t want it to interfere w/ the editors) on the click</p>
<p><code><br />
//add "media" buttons to metabox<br />
$('.custom_upload_buttons a').each(function() {<br />
$(this).click(function() {</p>
<p>				mediaid = $(this).parent().next('textarea').attr('id');		</p>
<p>				window.send_to_editor = window.send_to_editor_clone;<br />
});</p>
<p>				window.send_to_editor_clone = function(html){<br />
tinyMCE.execInstanceCommand(mediaid, 'mceInsertContent', false, html);<br />
tb_remove();<br />
}<br />
});<br />
</code></p>
</div><!-- .comment-text -->
</li><!-- .comment -->
