<div class="comment-text">
<p>@aaron- thanks!  i need it.  the following gets the ID numbers to properly increment.. had to go back to the i++ counter since livequery doesn&#8217;t support an index like .each().  i was hoping that would solve it, and the tinymce buttons do appear, but they don&#8217;t do anything yet, nor do they allow the textarea to be edited.  </p>
<p><code><br />
var i=1; </p>
<p>				$('.customEditor textarea').livequery(function(){</p>
<p>					$ta = $(this);<br />
id = $ta.parent().attr('id');</p>
<p>					if (!id){<br />
id = 'customEditor-' + i++;<br />
$ta.attr('id',id);<br />
}</p>
<p>					if($ta.parent().hasClass('minimal')){<br />
tinyMCE.settings = tinymceConfigs[1];<br />
} else {<br />
tinyMCE.settings = settings;<br />
}<br />
tinyMCE.execCommand('mceAddControl', true, id);</p>
<p>				})//end livequery<br />
</code></p>
</div><!-- .comment-text -->
