<a href="http://driftindustries.ca" rel="external nofollow" title="Anthony Clark"><img alt='Anthony Clark' src='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/72dd378f323ff1ac95b17156899d0f16?s=80&#038;r=r' srcset='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/72dd378f323ff1ac95b17156899d0f16?s=160&amp;r=r 2x' class='avatar avatar-80 photo' height='80' width='80' /></a><div class="comment-meta comment-meta-data"><span class="comment-author vcard"><cite class="fn" title="http://driftindustries.ca"><a href="http://driftindustries.ca" title="Anthony Clark" class="url" rel="external nofollow">Anthony Clark</a></cite></span><!-- .comment-author .vcard --> <span class="published"><abbr class="comment-date" title="Monday, May 16th, 2011, 1:57 pm">May 16, 2011</abbr> at <abbr class="comment-time" title="Monday, May 16th, 2011, 1:57 pm">1:57 pm</abbr></span> | <a class="permalink" href="http://www.farinspace.com/multiple-wordpress-wysiwyg-visual-editors/#comment-15728" title="Permalink to comment 15728">Permalink</a>  </div>
<div class="comment-text">
<p>@Aaron</p>
<p>I was able to figure out a solution that I hope works for everyone, there might be a better way, but it doesn&#8217;t require a lot of tweaking.  </p>
<p>The main issue with the cloning was the fact it was cloning the DOM after TinyMCE was run on the hidden editor to be cloned.  I tweaked the jQuery to only apply TinyMCE to the visible editors, leaving the editor to be copied as unaltered HTML.</p>
<p>You can view the updated jQuery on <a href="http://pastebin.com/FuUk3B2j" onclick="_gaq.push(['_trackEvent', 'outbound-comment', 'http://pastebin.com/FuUk3B2j', 'Pastebin']);" rel="nofollow">Pastebin</a>.</p>
</div><!-- .comment-text -->
