<li id="comment-17466" class="comment even thread-even depth-1 reader has-avatar">
<img alt='Sarah' src='http://2.gravatar.com/avatar/b994e14251e58a575ac36ab701f94957?s=80&#038;r=r' srcset='http://2.gravatar.com/avatar/b994e14251e58a575ac36ab701f94957?s=160&amp;r=r 2x' class='avatar avatar-80 photo' height='80' width='80' /><div class="comment-meta comment-meta-data"><span class="comment-author vcard"><cite class="fn">Sarah</cite></span><!-- .comment-author .vcard --> <span class="published"><abbr class="comment-date" title="Wednesday, August 24th, 2011, 6:12 am">August 24, 2011</abbr> at <abbr class="comment-time" title="Wednesday, August 24th, 2011, 6:12 am">6:12 am</abbr></span> | <a class="permalink" href="http://www.farinspace.com/multiple-wordpress-wysiwyg-visual-editors/#comment-17466" title="Permalink to comment 17466">Permalink</a>  </div>
<div class="comment-text">
<p>@ kathy and others that have been having problems with the html being printed instead of being executed.</p>
<p>Using  <code>wptexturize</code> and then <code>wpautop</code> on the user input <strong>before sending the content to the database&lt;/storng and then <code>esc_html($mb-&gt;get_the_value());</code> for displaying the content in the metabox seems to work for me.</p>
<p>Can someone else confirm that this works in their case too?</p>
<p>I can provide example code if anyone needs it.</strong></p>
</div><!-- .comment-text -->
</li><!-- .comment -->
