<li id="comment-21096" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1 reader has-avatar">
<img alt='Joseph' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/625030a9f3cb4182de58fcefe51ef060?s=80&#038;r=r' srcset='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/625030a9f3cb4182de58fcefe51ef060?s=160&amp;r=r 2x' class='avatar avatar-80 photo' height='80' width='80' /><div class="comment-meta comment-meta-data"><span class="comment-author vcard"><cite class="fn">Joseph</cite></span><!-- .comment-author .vcard --> <span class="published"><abbr class="comment-date" title="Friday, January 13th, 2012, 6:28 pm">January 13, 2012</abbr> at <abbr class="comment-time" title="Friday, January 13th, 2012, 6:28 pm">6:28 pm</abbr></span> | <a class="permalink" href="http://www.farinspace.com/multiple-wordpress-wysiwyg-visual-editors/#comment-21096" title="Permalink to comment 21096">Permalink</a>  </div>
<div class="comment-text">
<p>I had an issue with displaying output content from a textarea box, the line breaks show correctly in the textarea box after saving and shows correctly in the database as well but when display all breaks are remove.</p>
<p>I solved this by using for the display<br />
echo nl2br($custom_mb-&gt;get_the_value(&#8216;composer&#8217;));<br />
instead of<br />
$custom_mb-&gt;the_value(&#8216;composer&#8217;);</p>
<p>I&#8217;m not sure why this solved the problem, but I thought that it could be useful for someone looking for a solution for a similar issue.</p>
</div><!-- .comment-text -->
</li><!-- .comment -->
