<li id="comment-37662" class="comment even thread-even depth-1 reader has-avatar">
<img alt='Thilo' src='http://2.gravatar.com/avatar/8d11e5fb9275452b8b19a2c318d132f1?s=80&#038;r=r' srcset='http://2.gravatar.com/avatar/8d11e5fb9275452b8b19a2c318d132f1?s=160&amp;r=r 2x' class='avatar avatar-80 photo' height='80' width='80' /><div class="comment-meta comment-meta-data"><span class="comment-author vcard"><cite class="fn">Thilo</cite></span><!-- .comment-author .vcard --> <span class="published"><abbr class="comment-date" title="Saturday, May 14th, 2016, 3:00 am">May 14, 2016</abbr> at <abbr class="comment-time" title="Saturday, May 14th, 2016, 3:00 am">3:00 am</abbr></span> | <a class="permalink" href="http://www.farinspace.com/multiple-wordpress-wysiwyg-visual-editors/#comment-37662" title="Permalink to comment 37662">Permalink</a>  </div>
<div class="comment-text">
<p>This worked for me:</p>
<p>$mb-&gt;the_field(&#8216;new_content&#8217;);</p>
<p>$content_settings = array(<br />
&#8216;textarea_rows&#8217; =&gt; 15,<br />
&#8216;textarea_name&#8217; =&gt; $mb-&gt;get_the_name()<br />
);</p>
<p>wp_editor(htmlspecialchars_decode($mb-&gt;get_the_value()), &#8216;onepager-content&#8217;, $content_settings);</p>
</div><!-- .comment-text -->
</li><!-- .comment -->
